  "prompt": "If I got a minor customs infraction when entering Canada, do other countries like China or France know about the customs infraction that I got?",
  "response": "Typically, customs infractions and violations are recorded in a country\u2019s immigration or customs system, but they are not universally shared or accessible by other countries. Each country has its own systems and protocols for handling customs violations, and while major infractions might be shared internationally under certain conditions (like serious criminal activities), minor customs infractions generally remain within the country where they occurred.\n\nFor example, if you received a minor customs infraction in Canada, it is unlikely that China or France would have access to that information unless it has been reported through international law enforcement channels or if you were flagged for travel. However, it\u2019s always best to check the specific entry requirements and regulations of the countries you plan to visit, as they may have their own policies regarding past customs infractions.",
